title: Print, "Female Head, Year 1937 Collar", 1937
description:
Recto: This head-and-neck left profile view features a close-fitting headdress with an ear flap; and a collar, perhaps fabricated of metal, displaying the numerals 1, 9, 3, and 7, separated by vertical lines in groups of three. Three narrow, triangular shapes comprise a drop earring, extending downward from behind the flap.

Verso: "Copper" is handwritten on the lower right.

tombstone.epitaph: Print, "Female Head, Year 1937 Collar", 1937.29.5 x 23.2 cm (11 5/8 x 9 1/8 in.). Gift of Ellen Gustav Jensen. 1956-47-148.
